- **Name**: cache-performance-benchmark
- **Title**: Create cache hit/miss performance benchmark
- **Acceptance Criteria** (all must pass for APPROVE):
  - AC6.3: Cache hit benchmark mean ≤50μs verified for warm cache scenario
  - Benchmark measures hit rate achieving ≥95%
  - Cache miss performance within 5% of baseline
  - CV < 10% for statistical stability

## QA Results
- **Tests passed**: True
- **Summary**: All cache performance benchmark acceptance criteria PASS. Implementation successfully validates: (1) Cache hit latency 16.61ns << 50μs target (AC6.3), (2) Hit rate 99% > 95% requirement, (3) Cache miss overhead 0.18% << 5% limit, (4) CV < 10% for all cache benchmarks (max 6.97%). Comprehensive test coverage includes 8 benchmark functions, automated validation script, and 41 unit tests covering edge cases (empty inputs, boundary values, hash collisions, concurrency, Unicode). All 462 library unit tests pass. One pre-existing test failure in unrelated benchmark suite (lru_eviction/10 CV=13.11%) does not affect cache_performance implementation.

## Code Review Results
- **Approved**: True
- **Blocking issues**: False
- **Summary**: All acceptance criteria met with excellent results. Cache hit latency: 16.46 ns (3,037x below 50μs target), hit rate: 99% (exceeds 95%), cache miss overhead: 0.18% (well below 5%), CV: 3.3% (below 10%). The implementation provides comprehensive benchmarks and automated validation. Non-blocking issues relate to test automation completeness and script robustness improvements.
- **Detailed issues**: `/Users/santoshkumarradha/Documents/agentfield/code/int-agentfield-examples/af-swe/example-pyrust/.worktrees/issue-20-cache-performance-benchmark/.artifacts/coding-loop/d38a1567/review-issues.md`
- **Debt items**:
  - [should_fix] Missing automated test validation for benchmark results: No programmatic test (tests/test_cache_performance.rs) that fails in CI if benchmarks don't meet acceptance criteria. Validation relies on manual script execution.
  - [should_fix] Hardcoded hit rate assumption in validation script: Validation script hardcodes '99/100 = 99%' message instead of dynamically calculating from benchmark results, risking false positives if benchmark implementation changes.
  - [should_fix] Incomplete error handling for missing baseline: When compiler baseline is missing, script sets COMPILER_MEAN=0 and skips overhead check, but still uses it in summary calculations (lines 151-152), potentially causing misleading output.
  - [suggestion] Incorrect AC reference in benchmark comment: Comment references 'AC3.1' but should reference 'AC6.3' based on validation script and issue description.
  - [suggestion] Missing module-level documentation: No module-level doc comment explaining benchmark suite purpose, methodology, or configuration choices (e.g., why sample_size=200, measurement_time=10s).
